<section class="section">
  <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
    <a href="/">Home</a>
    <span>/</span>
    <span>About</span>
  </nav>

  <div class="about-split">
    <div>
      <h1>About This Site</h1>

      <p class="prose-width">
        Exonumist.com is a personal reference site for my collection of transportation tokens,
        with a focus on New York City transit history. My interest in tokens grew out of a long
        fascination with the New York City subway and the everyday objects connected to its history.
      </p>
    </div>

    <aside class="about-aside">
      <h3>Site Focus</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>NYC transit tokens</li>
        <li>Undocumented material, errors, and oddities</li>
        <li>Collector research</li>
      </ul>
    </aside>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="about-split">
    <div>
      <h2>My Collection</h2>

      <p class="prose-width">
        While this site currently focuses on New York City transportation exonumia, my broader collection
        includes Arcade, Hard Times, Civil War, Merchant, and Miscellaneous tokens — basically, interesting
        shiny metal things with history behind them.
      </p>

      <p class="prose-width">
        Cataloged transportation material follows the Atwood-Coffee Catalogue where applicable.
        Undocumented items are included when they help document discoveries, varieties, errors,
        oddities, or related collecting areas.
      </p>
      <p class="prose-width">
        Have something I may be interested in? See my
        <a href="/wanted/">Want List</a>.
      </p>
    </div>

    <aside class="about-aside">
      <h3>Also Collecting</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Civil War tokens</li>
        <li>Hard Times tokens</li>
        <li>Merchant tokens</li>
        <li>Arcade tokens</li>
        <li>Miscellaneous exonumia</li>
      </ul>
    </aside>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <h2>Free to Use</h2>

  <p class="prose-width">
    The goal of this site is to make the collection easy to browse, study, and share.
  </p>

  <p class="prose-width">
    Unless otherwise noted, the original photos, descriptions, and site content on Exonumist.com
    may be freely used, copied, downloaded, shared, and adapted for personal, educational,
    research, and collector use. Credit to Exonumist.com is appreciated when practical.
  </p>

  <p class="prose-width">
    Some catalog names, historical references, and identifying information may come from published
    references or collector terminology. Those sources remain the property of their respective
    authors or publishers.
  </p>

  <p class="prose-width">
    Corrections, additions, and attribution requests are welcome.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <h2>Research & References</h2>

  <p class="section-intro">
    References and organizations useful for transportation token research and catalog information.
  </p>

  <div class="grid-narrow">
    {% for resource in resources | sort(attribute="order") %}
      {% if resource.pub != false %}
        <a class="card-link" href="{{ resource.urlRef | resolveUrlRef(site) }}">
          <article class="resource-card resource-card-with-media">
            <div class="resource-card-body">
              <strong>{{ resource.title }}</strong>
              <p>{{ resource.text }}</p>
            </div>

            {% if resource.image %}
              <div class="resource-card-media">
                <img
                  class="resource-card-logo"
                  src="{{ resource.image }}"
                  alt="{{ resource.title }}" />
              </div>
            {% endif %}
          </article>
        </a>
      {% endif %}
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</section>
